DESCRIPTION:New lecture titles never before presented in Seattle: May 5th -
	 "This Just In: Latest Discoveries in the Universe" - The title says it al
	l. Drawn from within the previous two or three years of cosmic discovery -
	 with topics hand-picked for their impact on science and on the public's f
	ascinating with this moving frontier. May 6th - "Science as a Way of Knowi
	ng" - The anatomy of science: What it is. How it works. Why it works. And 
	why it's the most successful means of decoding nature that has ever been d
	evised. Learn further what social\, cultural\, and political forces stimul
	ate or thwart this moving frontier\, and what this bodes for the future of
	 nations and our species.\nMetal detectors & bag search at door. Arrive ea
